26/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO lobbyist Bruce Jackson, who serves as president of the Project on Transitional Democracies, said Thursday (25 September) that Macedonia has made good progress in reforming its defence sector. Jackson discussed preparations for NATO membership with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and will attend the weekend summit in Ohrid of the four Adriatic Charter signatories: Macedonia, Albania, Croatia and the United States.
In other news Thursday, the Croatian government adopted an action plan for NATO membership for the period 2003-2004. It incorporates political, economic, military and legislative reform measures. (Dnevnik - 26/09/03; MIA, HINA - 25/09/03)
